    "narrative": "The **Zurich Zebras** enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Christian Yelich** (72.61) and **Trea Turner** (71.43). **Christian Yelich** draws a prime matchup against Littell; despite a neutral park, his elite platoon advantage (13% boost) makes him our strongest start. **Trea Turner** remains locked in at the top of the order, and while he faces a formidable arm in Gallen, his leadoff placement provides a 10% efficiency cushion that sustains his value despite the tough SP_xERA. **Caleb Durbin** (67.85) and **Kyle Schwarber** (67.82) are also standout plays today. **Caleb Durbin** specifically benefits from an ideal wind-out environment and a high-leverage spot against Pallante, while **Kyle Schwarber** continues to command a high efficiency score driven by his elite xwOBA metrics, mitigating the risk of facing Gallen.\n\nWe have a clear platoon strategy in effect today, favoring **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (61.24) and **Josh Smith** (62.01), both of whom receive massive 14% boosts from dynamic platoon modeling against right-handed pitching. Conversely, **Yordan Alvarez** (55.60) is a moderate play despite his pedigree; the matchup against the elite Logan Gilbert creates significant SP-skill friction (-19%), forcing him into our lower-tier start category today. The most difficult personnel decision involved the bench, where **Victor Scott II** (58.31) fell just shy of replacing **Kazuma Okamoto** (58.71) or **Dillon Dingler** (48.11). While **Victor Scott II** offers the high-speed upside critical to our stolen base strategy, his projected 9th-hole placement created an 8% anchor on his total score, causing the optimizer to favor the higher lineup placement of **Kazuma Okamoto** to maximize volume.\n\nRisk management remains a priority given the volatility of our matchup against Gallen. While **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** carry the load, both must contend with a pitcher capable of suppressing damage. **Dillon Dingler** and **Logan O'Hoppe** are currently slotted as marginal plays; owners should monitor the wind data closely, as any shift toward an inward breeze would likely drop **Caleb Durbin** and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** out of the optimal starting threshold. We are keeping **Victor Scott II**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Carson Benge**, and **Hyeseong Kim** ready in reserve, though **Hyeseong Kim** is strictly avoided today given the brutal matchup against deGrom.",
